# Backend Environment Configuration

## Development

```env
DEBUG=True
SECRET_KEY=django-insecure-kyc-secret-key-change-in-production
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///db.sqlite3
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:3000,http://127.0.0.1:5173
```

## Staging

```env
DEBUG=False
SECRET_KEY=your-secure-random-key-here
ALLOWED_HOSTS=staging.example.com,www.staging.example.com
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@db.staging.example.com:5432/kyc_db
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://staging.example.com,https://www.staging.example.com
EMAIL_BACKEND=django.core.mail.backends.smtp.EmailBackend
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-app-password
```

## Production

```env
DEBUG=False
SECRET_KEY=your-super-secure-random-key-here-min-50-chars
ALLOWED_HOSTS=example.com,www.example.com
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@db.example.com:5432/kyc_db
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://example.com,https://www.example.com
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=True
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=True
CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE=True
EMAIL_BACKEND=django.core.mail.backends.smtp.EmailBackend
EMAIL_HOST=your-smtp-provider.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-email
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-password
SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-key@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0
```

## Configuration Variables

### Core Django
- `DEBUG`: Set to False in production
- `SECRET_KEY`: Generate with: `python -c "from django.core.management.utils import get_random_secret_key; print(get_random_secret_key())"`
- `ALLOWED_HOSTS`: Comma-separated domain list

### Database
- `DATABASE_URL`: Format varies by backend:
  - SQLite: `sqlite:///path/to/db.sqlite3`
  - PostgreSQL: `postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/dbname`
  - MySQL: `mysql://user:pass@host:3306/dbname`

### Frontend
- `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`: Comma-separated frontend URLs

### Security
- `SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT`: Redirect HTTP to HTTPS
- `SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE`: Cookies only over HTTPS
- `CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE`: CSRF cookies only over HTTPS

### Email (Optional)
- `EMAIL_BACKEND`: Default is console backend
- `EMAIL_HOST`: SMTP server hostname
- `EMAIL_PORT`: SMTP server port
- `EMAIL_USE_TLS`: Use TLS encryption
- `EMAIL_HOST_USER`: SMTP username
- `EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD`: SMTP password or app password

### Monitoring (Optional)
- `SENTRY_DSN`: Sentry error tracking

## Setting Environment Variables

### Development (Django settings.py)
```python
import os
from decouple import config

DEBUG = config('DEBUG', default=True, cast=bool)
SECRET_KEY = config('SECRET_KEY', default='dev-key-not-secure')
ALLOWED_HOSTS = config('ALLOWED_HOSTS', default='localhost,127.0.0.1').split(',')
```

### Linux/Mac
```bash
export DEBUG=False
export SECRET_KEY=your-key
python manage.py runserver
```

### Windows PowerShell
```powershell
$env:DEBUG="False"
$env:SECRET_KEY="your-key"
python manage.py runserver
```

### Docker
```dockerfile
ENV DEBUG=False
ENV SECRET_KEY=your-key
```

### .env File (with python-decouple)
```bash
pip install python-decouple
```

Create `.env`:
```
DEBUG=False
SECRET_KEY=your-key
ALLOWED_HOSTS=example.com
```

Access in code:
```python
from decouple import config
debug = config('DEBUG', default=True, cast=bool)
```

## Security Checklist

Before deploying to production:

- [ ] Change SECRET_KEY to a secure random value
- [ ] Set DEBUG=False
- [ ] Update ALLOWED_HOSTS
- [ ] Configure database (use PostgreSQL, not SQLite)
- [ ] Enable HTTPS (SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=True)
- [ ] Set secure cookie flags
- [ ] Configure email backend
- [ ] Set up error monitoring (Sentry)
- [ ] Use environment-specific settings
- [ ] Regularly rotate secrets
- [ ] Keep dependencies updated
- [ ] Run security checks: `python manage.py check --deploy`

## Generate Secure Secret Key

```bash
python -c "from django.core.management.utils import get_random_secret_key; print(get_random_secret_key())"
```

Or use:
```bash
openssl rand -base64 32
```

## Database Connection Strings

### PostgreSQL
```
postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/kyc_db
```

### MySQL
```
mysql://username:password@localhost:3306/kyc_db
```

### SQLite
```
sqlite:///./db.sqlite3
```

## CORS Configuration

### Development
```
http://localhost:3000
http://localhost:5173
http://127.0.0.1:3000
```

### Production
```
https://yourdomain.com
https://www.yourdomain.com
```

## Email Provider Examples

### Gmail
```
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-app-password
```

### AWS SES
```
EMAIL_HOST=email-smtp.region.amazonaws.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-access-key
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-secret-key
```

### SendGrid
```
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=apikey
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-sendgrid-api-key
```

## Monitoring & Logging

### Sentry (Error Tracking)
```
SENTRY_DSN=https://key@sentry.io/project-id
```

### CloudWatch (AWS)
```
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret
```

### DataDog
```
DD_API_KEY=your-api-key
DD_APP_KEY=your-app-key
```
